At Magunga Youth Empowerment Centre, which is located within the same compound, the suspects stole musical instruments.
A piano, amplifier, mixer, and extension cables were stolen from the building.
A report about a break-in was also reported at Magunga Health Centre where a computer was stolen from the facility’s laboratory.
Business operators at Magunga trading centre also reported that their shops were broken into.
Among traders who lost property were bookshop owners.
“Others reported that there were attempts to break into their shops,” Mr Maina said.

